In those platforms that require the OS singleton to be `created/destroyed` dynamically by calling `new/delete`, the memory pool manager is destroyed before the OS singleton, causing that those objects in the singleton that were created using the memory pool manager, fail to be freed.

For instance the OS singleton in the iOS platform

```
int iphone_main(int width, int height, int argc, char** argv) {
    //...
    os = new OSIPhone(width, height);
    //...
};

void iphone_finish() {
    printf("iphone_finish\n");
    Main::cleanup(); // <-- this destroys the memory pool manager
    delete os; // ... but the manager is needed here
};
```

The error reported by Godot for this error is:

```
ERROR: free_static: Condition ' !MemoryPoolStatic::get_singleton() ' is true.
   At: /Users/rhodylugo/Desktop/Godot/core/os/memory.cpp:58.
```
